===Etymology 2===
Greek [[πόλος]] "axis of rotation"

====Noun====
'''pole''' (''plural:'' [[poles]])

#An extreme point, usually magnetically or geographically. ([[North pole]], [[South pole]])
#A difference of potential between two contacts on a source of electrical power. ([[plus]] [[minus]])

